Yo!
Haven't really posted anything lately, but ya know what? GET OVER IT! .... yeah....
Right now it is raining outside, I'm at the desk in Curves, listening to Cher crap remix music, but trying to listen to the rain instead. I'm listening to my thoughts and all those things going on in my head too, but I try to block them out so I don't start crying. I never realized how much I love living here and how amazing some of the people are. I'm going to miss so many of them so badly I don't dare think about it. Especially in public, because I might just burst into tears and then people would think I was some crazy schitzo lady or something. I love this area and it will always be part of my life. The people, the weather, the driving, the sites, everything. All of it I will miss with the deep regret. I think I know that if I don't move I will go back to being bored and depressed and missing Washington again. Except lately I've been thinking to myself, why am I moving? Really, what is the reason? What is my excuse? And to tell you the truth, I have no idea. When I think ahead to when I'm settled in Shoreline, I want to cry because I feel that I will be lonely and bored and out of place. I will not fit in with my family there. I am not a Christian and I am not someone to be molded to fit. I feel that if I refuse to do something I will make it completely miserable for myself and my family. If I refuse to go to church I will have no where to stay, I will have no way to get to work, I will have no one. No one except Catie and she has work and school. I won't have my Mom, I won't have my Maddie, my Alana, my Pader, my Teddy. No one. I will be alone. Completely alone and that's what I feel like right now. I feel that everyone is trying to distance themselves from me. I decide to move, it's a week before I move and I am making new friends and a guy tells me that he wishes I wasn't moving and kisses me. What am I to do? Say "HEY EVERYONE! I'm not moving!" Then they'll just see me as some poor undecided fool who has nothing, who can't stick with one decision, and then things will go back to the way they were before I made this fatefull decision to leave this place. It will all go back to me sitting at home, doing nothing. I won't have a job, I won't have school. People won't pay attention because, hey, I'm not moving. So what am I to do? Huh? What? I don't know, I don't think I'll ever know. 
How do I say that I miss you already. And when I think of leaving you and possibly never seeing you again, it makes my heart hollow and my head spin, my eyes tearful and my breath fast. If I visit will I see you? 
I wish I could forget it all.

When I thought the music here couldn't get any worse someone asks me to put on the Cher cd....it's "A Tribute to a Diva" I want to hurl all over people. Especially those who put this piece of shit together. It's Cher singing, but they've sped it up to horrible horribleness. Please put me out of my misery. I think I spelled that wrong....oh well. 

I am so tired! I want to be home! I had to open this morning. =( All I want is a bed with a blanket. Please? I couldn't be happier that it's Friday though! I'm even happier though because I don't have to stay until 11 this morning I get to go home at 8:30! Another lady's covering for me this morning because I covered for her last night. Yep, yesterday I worked from 7am-11am, went home and then I worked 5pm-7:30pm. I was so tired last night, I fell asleep right when my head hit the pillow. It was lovely, but then Coco decided to bark her highest in the middle of the night. It was nice...

I am so tired and I've hardly eatan(sp?) today. That's my fault, but oh well. French fries sound SO nummy right now. But what kind of circuit trainer would I be if I left and brought back french fries? LOL! That would actually be kind of funny.  But I can't. Dad bought my ticket today though =D so that makes me VERY excited and happy! I called a couple Curves in Shoreline and they're going to mail me an application to fill out and then I'm going to mail it back and hopefully I can get a job at one of them! I still have so much to do! Aahh. I need to go through my crap and get rid of some of it, hopefully half of it. I then have to pack the remainder of my crap into boxes and luggage. I have to I have way to much shit. What am I going to do with it all? I need to get an address change thing. Blah blah blah.
When I leave on the 21st it's going to be the last time I see my mom until May =( But it'll be alright. 
Someone is honking outside like a moron and I am going to go crazy! Or it might be in the music. Either one it's driving me mad! 
I can hardly wait until December! I will miss somethings about this place. But not a lot and not for very long. 
=D

So today I woke up at about 2 it was nice. Then I ate some food and vaccuumed or however you spell it. That was cool.....
Then I took the dogs for a little walk. Came home showered super fast and got my shit together for some halloween parties we went to.
Then we left.
First  we met one of moms friends and we were supposed to go walk around Fort Mason or somewhere. Moms friend had told us she would be staying in a youth hostel neat there, but what she ment is that she'd be staying there next week and she was actually staying in a hostel way far away in the down town part of SF so we drove everywhere trying to find it. While we were driving all around we drove past this guy walking up the sidewalk and I swear to god it was RYAN GOSLING! I wanted to stop but there was no where to pull over and there were a bunch of cars behind us. Sad huh? He was so hot. 
So we got there and moms friend was a bitch and quite annoying so we didn't hang out with her long...thank goodness. And she isn't really moms friend because mom doesn't really like her. Well not anymore now that she's spent more time with her.
But while we were there I met this gorgeous german guy named Dierk(probably spelled that completely wrong) who has an internship somewhere in SF and had a friend visiting and staying at that hostel. He was so hot and I think he thought I was too so that made the visit with the crazy lady worth while.
Then we left and went to Laura and Toms party. Again it took us forever to find their place and we drove all over the other half of SF trying to find it. We finally found it and parking and it was a lot of fun. But then we made the mistake of leaving there early and going to Sinems party. It took us about an hour to find it and when we finally did, it took us another 45minutes to find parking so that was awesome. Then we had to walk about 30minutes to the location adn when we finally got inside it was really fucking lame. We didn't see anyone we knew so we used the bathroom-which was a toilet in a closet-and left. Then we came home and now I'm sad and bored =(

and NO ONE has come in! IT's AWESOME! I don't want anyone to come in. I like it so much better this way. I can listen to good music and not shit. Sweeeeeeeeeeet!
But I'm sort of sad because Jessi whose the manager here isn't going to be working here after the 31st =( She's really nice and I relate better with her because she's closer to my age. =( She was really nice too. She's the one who hired me and shit. Oh well I guess. I'm going to be working mornings now so that means I have to get up at 6am almost every morning. Wait...no...EVERY morning. Sweet.
LOL! Oh well I guess. I'll be working about 68 hours a month now =D scary
I guess I'll get on a better schedule yeah?

If I didn't work here I would tell people to go to a different one. 
Well on a happier note, have I told you how much I love my icon thing? It's awesome!

When I finally got here this morning I was coming up the stairs and wearing my stupid crocks I caught the toe of my shoe on the edge of the step and went down. Catching myself with my hand and elbow/forearm. Now my hand REALLY fucking hurts. My arm is ok thought. 
If I was wearing any other shoes I would have been able to catch myself without falling. But these shoes are fucking ridiculous.

It's name was Toby. So adorable! It was so sweet! I want one of those, a Scotty and a corgi! A bucnh of little short legged weirdos! lol! Then I work in the evening also. So I open and close. I'm eating a Curves Granola Bar! They're not that bad, but they're terrible for my jaw. Oh well. So Maddie gets to go up to WA at the end of this month! for almost a week! =( 
Oh well again.

Ok, So I am so goddamn sick of Maddie turning on lights and being loud and then asking me to take the dogs out when she has plenty of time to do it herself.  Why? Why is she so inconsiderate? I don't understand. If I was loud or turned lights on she would freak out! But it's ok for her to do it? Everytime I wake up before her if it's early in the morning or in the late afternoon I am always sure that I don't wake her up. I hardly ever turn on a light or make much noise. I could have had 2 extra hours of sleep today, but she woke me up and then I couldn't get back to sleep because I was so upset and all I could think of was slapping her. Then she comes in all sweet, "Beth can you take the dogs out? I'm supposed to be at work like now." 
Then she doesn't leave until like a half an hour later. But she didn't take them out. I was going to say something to her but then she left. Goddamn it! She ruined my whole morning!
For some reason I just thought of Christmas shopping and I can't wait! I love getting gifts for people! I can hardly wait until Christmas time! We're taking the TRAIN up to Washington! It's going to be so pretty! It's gonna be all snowy and pretty in the passes! I love the Holidays! I love the cold and the bundling up and hot coco or coffee! MMMM! I want coffee! I can't wait to move back up to Washington. May or June! That's a really long time from now =( I wish it was next month. I miss the Puget Sound. I miss Seattle. Seattle sparkles clean compared to Berkeley and San Francisco. Hahaha! 
According to the scale we have at work I've lost 5 pounds! Fuckin Sweet!
I don't want to be at work. I want to be home sleeping. I wish this place didn't suck and I wish people wouldn't come in. blah blah!
yadda yadda. crappidy crap.

Don't you just love it when your neighbors get your mail, keep it for a couple months and then throught it over your wall when it's raining and after they've read it?
It's my favorite thing.
So if you're wondering what the hell I'm talking about I shall explain.
.

So Maddie subscribed to Scientific American in the middle of July and expected to get the August issue. It was an issue that she really wanted because it had several interesting articles in it, but she never got it. We were puzzled to why she never got it because she had sent the subscription card in early enough. We thought maybe mom had forgotten to pay for the subscription so she renewed it. She was going to backorder the issue which would have cost $10 plus shipping or something, but they decided against it. 
Today I wake up...late as always around 1 or 1:30...and I'm about to go for a walk in the pooring rain when I see that there's an issue of Scientific American on our patio completely soaked through. I go out, pick it up and set it down on our carpet inside the door and think how pissed Maddie's going to be when she gets home and sees it. Then I think nothing more of it.
Then when mom gets home I point it out to her and she asks what month it is. I hadn't checked earlier so I did. Oh and what'd'ya know! It's AUGUST!
So mom and I look at eachother and she says "Maddie is going to go up there and rip Owen a new asshole!"  Or something along those lines. Mom called Tom our landlord and talked to him and since we all know Owen is an aggresive asshole he told her to tell Maddie that if he does anything like reach for her, hit her or even gets in her face that Tom would be there within an hour with an evidtion notice. And the same for Maddie if she starts something. Blah blah blah. I don't want to type anymore. I'm going to go exercise.

So. Mom and I are on our way home from a movie (Pan's Labyrinth)and we're talking about people getting stabbed with broken bottles(you'll just have to see the movie to know why or I'll tel you later) and she just casually mentions that she dated a guy in high school who had stabbed someone with a broken bottle. 
Not only that, but she was with him when he did it. She didn't SEE him do it, but she was in his truck while him and his friend went and faught some other guys after a kegger on some road in the middle of the woods....interesting huh?
YEAH! Sheesh!
She said at the party there had been some tention between her boyfriend(Jim) and this guy. 
After a while at the party they decide to leave. Jim's driving, my mother's in the middle and their friend Joe(one of crazy grandmas crazy nazi ex-boyfriend's sons) on the other side of her. The guy her boyfriend was not liking pulled up behind them with some friends. So Jim stopped and told mom to stay in the car, grabbed a bottle and him and Joe got out of the car......hm? I wonder what happened next?
While Jim and Joe were out fighting these guys mom just sat in the car and waited. I was just like "WHY?! HOW!?" I don't see how someone could just stay in the car when they knew that their boyfriend was outside fighting some guy. Wouldn't you, like, atleast stick your head out the window and ask them to stop or something? When I asked mom this, she was just " Probably because I was half ass drunk...and because I didn't want to see guys fighting." 
I was laughing soooo hard! 
But, if you are asking "If she wasn't out there with them, how does she know he stabbed some guy with a broken bottle?"
Well, smart ass, she saw him take the bottle and the next week when she went to school Jim wasn't there and someone told her he was in Juvenile-whatever-you-call-it. 
So yeah.
My mother has dated a guy that stabbed some other guy with a broken bottle. And her best friend's dad was a Nazi...and his brothers were big huge scary BIKERS! No. Not Bicyclists. Bikers. As in Motorcycles!
Sheesh! My mother is crazy awesome and I love her.

Yesterday we went to the Northern CA Renaissance Faire! It was SOOOOOOOOOO much fun! There were tons of people and like 95% of them were in costume. There were some really nasty looking people(by 'people' I mean whores), but it was fun seeing all the different costumes.
There was this little kid who was about 10-yrs-old who had a little dalmationy colored mouse with him. It was so adorable! He walked up to me and mom and was just all "Good day madames! Don't be afraid, she won't bite. You can pet her if you want to!" Then he put the mouse on his head and the mouse just sat there and let me pet it. It was so cute! The kid was in this really cool peasant boy costume. It's so funny because all the kids that grew up going to the faire or with parents that participate in it are called "faire brats". There was also lots of pirates and lots of guys in kilts.
We didn't get to the jousting and that's kinda sad, but we didn't exactly know where it was and when we realised that it was going on it was like 20 minutes into it already. The lady that played Queen Elizabeth wasn't that great but it was still cool. 
On a super duper awesome note!
I GOT A BODICE!!!!
Mom got it for me for my birthday! YAY! It's sooo pretty! It's suede! It was one of the nicest ones there and it was the cheapest one too! Cheapest as in price; )
They had corsets....real corsets! for only $73!
They were sooooo pretty! I almost bought one but I didn't have enough, and plus the one I wanted was too big. There was some really nice clothing there, but there was also some really crappy-polyester-halloween-costume clothes too. It was so much fun!
I hope we get to go next year! : )

Tomorrow MOM and I are going to the Northern California Renaissance Faire! I'm sooo excited! It's going to be so much fun! It's in Hollister or Casa de Fruta or soemthing like that! There's going to be full contact Jousting! I want to see that sooo badly! There's going to be Archery! I love Archery! I've only done it once and that was forever ago, but it was so much fun! 
Must go now!
Tell you more after we get home tomorrow!
